Forces of the Mega Strike Gather
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will form their strike commission on Friday, which will be responsible for coordinating Monday's indefinite strike.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health insurance, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause significant traffic jams because the rail traffic will be stopped almost completely and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 13h.
The unions of the league will make known, on Friday afternoon, the details of their strike on Monday, organized with the National Association of workers' councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of the actions of Monday.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and, from Monday, organizations joining the strike will stop work indefinitely if they cannot reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health insurance, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the Health Insurance Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strikes.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide what action to take.
According to Monday's agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the Health Insurance Act will only take place late in the evening, or even at night.
Due to the strike scheduled for Monday, significant traffic jams are planned: the railways will stop working indefinitely and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Volán companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the track will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call for strikes, the list of them is constantly updated on the League website.
Some organizations report going on strike for an indefinite period, others have declared a temporary work stoppage.
Until Thursday afternoon the M<0xC3><0x81>V (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, but as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, Budapest public transport will strike from the start of service until 1 p.m., Budapest airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Union of Teachers and the Democratic Union of Teachers called for strikes for 8 hours and 2 hours respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country in turn, the Union of Health and Social Sector Employees (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will strike a two-hour warning.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, requires that the government withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new conception to the social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be implemented from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim is a guarantee for retirement before the legal age, which would allow the system to carry out the functions that it deserves before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning the secondary railway lines and the waiting for another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard has increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several aspects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “risk warning”, the company points out that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur as a result of the aggravation of the already existing ethnic tension between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard likely to provoke this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: “public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma affair to representatives of radical and extreme political groups who have based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians”.
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, in particular regarding confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following a greater publicity given to the reorganization of the Hungarian radical and extreme right groups since the autumn of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 giving themselves the name of "national self-defense association".
"The common feature of these rallies is that they define themselves as a civilian organization while they publicly declare the preparation of their adherents for defense missions (catastrophes, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, in addition, evoking the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words of the state," they added.
They pointed out that everything was happening according to the method which, based on the rancor of the society of politics and parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions under a civil aspect.
The emphasis on civil character and association status thus serves only to avoid the legal pitfalls of the registration of such associations in court but also constitutes a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a factor that also increases the risk in relation to neighbourly relations.
“In recent months, many neighbouring countries have cited the Hungarian Guard as a potential source of risk and the ultra-nationalist political actors of some neighbouring countries wish to justify their anti-Hungarian policy by referring to the Hungarian Guard’s constitution.
This influences the political stability of the region,” they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not a unique phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, political risks have increased throughout the region.
As they say, the functioning of the Hungarian Guard resembles, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard whose constitution was declared by the Bulgarian National Union (BNU) in August 2007.
The numerous Roma riots that erupted in a district of Sofia (Kraszna Poljana) are at the origin of the constitution of the Bulgarian guard.
Taking advantage of these events, the UNB decided to constitute a guard by saying that the objective of the organization is “national self-defense”.
According to them, in the last 17 years, the gypsies have “terrorized” Bulgaria but the state has remained inactive and neutral, recalls the Political Capital.
They added that the initiative had sparked lively debate in Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the statement by some organizations of Bulgarian Roma regarding the establishment of their own guard as a way of resistance signals the increased risk of ethnic clashes.
The operation of the Hungarian Guard showing similarities to that of the Bulgarian National Guard does not preclude Hungarian Roma from responding to the threat in the same way by organizing their own self-defense, one can read in the risk warning of Political Capital.
At the request of the telegraph agency, Attila Juhász, director of research at Political Capital, said: risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, their risk analysis is published every year and if events occur that could have an impact on the change in risk, they inform the public, as in this case, by issuing a risk warning.
The party is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holidays and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
The holidays are not uniform in the EU and the US either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national and state holidays and days of rest.
Days of rest are often linked to religious holidays or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, the latter all the more so that New Year's Eve can rest peacefully.
In one year, we have eleven holidays marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as well as October 23, which is the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1st is Labor Day and on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased family members and friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, at Pentecost and at Christmas.
Days of our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, depending on the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases where there is only one working day left before or after the holiday marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of extended weekends by working or going to school on the Saturday preceding the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in a special regulation on the replacement days of the days before or after the holidays.
The law extends to all employers and all their employees employed, to civil servants and to persons working in the public service.
It does not, however, apply to service societies, institutions that are continuously running and in service, because of their vocation, and also for days of rest.
This year, the working days will be changed only around the holidays: from December 24, life stops almost all over the country because according to experiences the majority of people rather do overtime or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes so that they can spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
Next year many holidays fall in the middle or at the end of the week, therefore there will be fewer changes in the level of working days compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized for the first time around Labor Day to allow employees to stay at home four days in a row.
Saturday 25 April will be a working day to have a day off on Friday 2 May.
Another change is scheduled for October 23: Saturday, October 18 will be a working day replacing Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if the day of the new year falls on a Wednesday.
Six futile things that can annoy colleagues terribly
Emails we forget to send, voicemails we never receive, innocent lies that annoy us almost more: these are things that “beautify” the daily life of a workplace.
The question is whether we get used to these problems or take up the challenge and consciously avoid ambiguous situations, causing trouble to others.
Examples.
“Excuse me, I forgot to tell you that you were called from the marketing department,” a colleague tells you.
That you missed a date?
At best he is sorry and tries to arrange things by calling the marketing department to tell them that he has forgotten to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, this is done with an apology.
Before you have any painful explanations, it is helpful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
Are you borrowing something that doesn’t belong to you?
There's nothing more annoying than wanting to take a file, an office tool or the phone and you can't find them anywhere.
Do you remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking otherwise they are right to be angry with you for stealing their property.
Do not bring envelopes, post-it in your pocket because it can be annoying that there are no more and you need them right away.
Are you talking about the privacy of your colleagues?
There are no good ways to stop gossip from spreading.
Who did what, with whom?
Or and why?
Don’t tell everyone your information (assumptions) about your colleagues’ privacy!
If a colleague shares their intimate secrets with you, do not abuse their trust!
Bury the shared information within yourself and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware of it.
Are you claiming to be sick for no good reason?
When you call the office and you declare yourself sick under the pretext of a tearful headache because you feel bad or you feel you need to rest that day, think about the fact that your work, your urgent business, your future missions must be carried out by someone else in your place.
Don't bother your colleagues!
If you know in advance that the next day you will not go to work or that something may happen that would force you to stay at home, do not forget to notify your boss and your colleagues to avoid them being surprised that you will be absent the next day.
Fucking, giggling, phone
You're immersing yourself in your work, but the laughter of your colleagues pulls you out of it brutally?
Did you unwittingly become a witness to a conversation over the phone that you would have done better not to listen to?
Do not disturb your co-workers with humming, humming, aloud discussions (which you conduct over their heads), flickering, gross words, or discontent expressed aloud.
They can be disturbing even if your colleagues are not immersed in a project (writing, design, organization).
Are you blaming others for a mistake?
If your work is not done for the set deadline, you forget to send a letter or an important message, do not blame anyone for this forgetting!
Don’t blame it on the possible chaos in the office or your noisy colleagues!
Recognize it if you made a mistake and if it presented inconveniences to others, repair the mistake!
Ask how you could fix your fault, fix the negligence!
Do you feel at home at the office too much?
Putting on a jog and slippers is comfortable at home but they are not suitable for the office!
Do not put on comfortable jogging even if your function allows it!
Do not be neglected, respect your colleagues and yourself by dressing properly, and if your function requires it by putting on nice and elegant clothes, to go to work!
