600 thousand people failed to renew their driving license in time
Six hundred thousand drivers allowed the deadline to expire and failed to renew their old driver's licenses whose validity expires at the end of the year.
We are on the last day when people can still apply for renewal, so that the authorities are in a position to issue them a new permit before the end of the year.
However, the Department is not afraid that hundreds of thousands of unlicensed drivers will be on the road.
According to the authorities, they have not renewed their driving licences especially those who no longer wish to drive.
As municipalities report a drop in the number of licence renewal applications, authorities in the capital are flooded with applications and the number of licence renewal applications has been increasing this week.
The City Hall satisfies about 2000 customers per day.
There's a tail of about half an hour.
In Prague, nearly 140.OO drivers have not yet renewed their driver's licenses.
The issuance of a new permit takes 20 days.
But it is possible to request the issue within a shortened period of five days.
In this case, the driver pays an additional five hundred crowns.
Drivers who fail to complete the mandatory renewal of their driver's license by the end of the year and will be driving on the road without a valid driver's license will face a fine as of January.
The culprit will be forced to pay two thousand crowns maximum.
However, the police officer can also deal with the offence using an amicable approach.
In the case of an administrative offence, the fine rises to 2,500 kroner.
According to former information, even a person who was not going to travel was liable to a fine.
In doing so, she could be forced to pay up to 30,000 crowns.
The Ministry had called on the authorities to exercise restraint and to impose fines not exceeding 1,000 kroner.
However, according to the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka, no one risks fines in the tens of thousands.
The driver's license is a document that people can use to decide whether they want to have it or not.
This is not like with the identity card, which must be valid without exceptions.
People who no longer want to drive should give their driver’s license.
It is enough to bring it or send it to the corresponding municipality.
Driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 will cease to be valid at the end of the year.
However, vehicle drivers are also forced to gradually renew other types of driving licences.
Persons holding documents dating from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to renew.
