What insurance is right for me?
Auto insurance, which covers the driver in the event of a loss, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, age of the driver's license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the right car.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, age of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the odds to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women must pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have lower claims rates due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of having an accident.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will present the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers him a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various drawbacks when entering into an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as poor driving experience and seniority of the driver's license.
Although the ideal way to be well-insured is full-risk insurance, there are other, more economical options.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for an all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they get the coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," specifies Luis Noguera, the manager in Spain of First Europa, online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
I'll give you some advice.
If you are under 25, try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will have an impact on the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and the company's profit.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses ", clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into an insurance contract, as the loss rate is reduced thanks to the experience accumulated.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose an all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people can not take advantage of the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates full-risk insurance, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claims rate, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have more casual driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” Noguera said.
For retirees an all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being this of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver against possible losses, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
